Lesson: Getting an xStatus Value <sub>(rxp-2.5.1)</sub> <ul> <li> <p>xAPI: xStatus Audio Volume</p> </li> <li> <p>Structure the xAPI command above into the URL under the Getting an xStatus request in your Postman collection.</p> </li> </ul> View properly formatted URL and Successful Response <p></p> Audio DefaultVolume URL <p>https://{{ device_ipAddress }}/getxml?location=Status/Audio/Volume</p> View Failed Response <p>Something to note on xStatus Get Requests, is you'll still get a 200 OK if your auth and IP are correct when talking to the Codec</p> <p>But a lack of response information can tell you that you may have a fault in your xAPI path in the URL</p> <p> What to expect for a bad path </p> <p> What to expect for a missing path </p> Lesson: Get multiple xStatus Values under a Common Node <sub>(rxp-2.5.2)</sub> <ul> <li> <p>xAPI: xStatus Audio</p> </li> <li> <p>Structure the xAPI command above into the URL under the Getting multiple xStatus Values under a Common Node request in your Postman collection.</p> </li> </ul> View properly formatted URL and Successful Response Audio DefaultVolume URL <p>https://{{ device_ipAddress }}/getxml?location=Status/Audio</p> View Successful HTTP Response <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0"?&gt;
&lt;Status product="Cisco Codec" version="ce11.20.1.7.913a6c7c769" apiVersion="4"&gt;
  &lt;Audio&gt;
    &lt;Devices&gt;
      &lt;Bluetooth&gt;
        &lt;ActiveProfile&gt;None&lt;/ActiveProfile&gt;
      &lt;/Bluetooth&gt;
      &lt;HandsetUSB&gt;
        &lt;ConnectionStatus&gt;NotConnected&lt;/ConnectionStatus&gt;
        &lt;Cradle&gt;OnHook&lt;/Cradle&gt;
      &lt;/HandsetUSB&gt;
      &lt;HeadsetUSB&gt;
        &lt;ConnectionStatus&gt;NotConnected&lt;/ConnectionStatus&gt;
        &lt;Description&gt;&lt;/Description&gt;
        &lt;Manufacturer&gt;&lt;/Manufacturer&gt;
      &lt;!-- And the List Goes On... --&gt;
  &lt;/Audio&gt;
&lt;/Status&gt;
</code></pre> View Failed Response <p>Something to note on xStatus Get Requests, is you'll still get a 200 OK if your auth and IP are correct when talking to the Codec</p> <p>But a lack of response information can tell you that you may have a fault in your xAPI path in the URL</p> <p> What to expect for a bad path </p> <p> What to expect for a missing path </p>

